The paper deals with triangulations and their flips, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of edge labels and the analysis of the diameter of the flip graph suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of the flip graph and its connectivity also relates to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
